title: zstaggerTo supports much more than just any[]
body:
Ref documentation found at http://greensock.com/docs/#/HTML5/GSAP/TweenMax/staggerTo/ 

An array of target objects whose properties should be affected, or selector text that gets passed to TweenLite.selector (for selecting DOM elements). For example, if jQuery (or similar) is loaded and you pass ".myClass", it would act as though you passed in an array of DOM elements that had the "myClass" class applied. The same behavior applies if you pass a jQuery object containing multiple elements (like $(".myClass")).

title: Microsoft Dynamics CRM Interface API
body: I've been using some form of a TypeScript definition file for Microsoft Dynamics CRM for 2 years.  In order to encourage more Dynamics CRM developers to seriously consider TypeScript as a preferable language to hook into its UI's extensibility model, I've completely done up these definition files from scratch, and liberally applied code documentation, which borrows heavily from the Microsoft's own API documentation, to ensure a high-quality experience.  Once the pull is accepted, I'm ready to go-live with a blog posting at crmentropy.blogspot.com that highlights some of the conventions I've taken with the definition (particularly around the use of Generics).
